1. Definitions
--------------

1.1. "Contributor"
    means each individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to
    the creation of, or covers Covered Software.

1.2. "Contributor Version"
    means the combination of the Contributions of others (if any) used
    by a Contributor and that Contributor's Contribution Date.

1.3. "Contribution"
    means Covered Software of a particular Contributor.

1.4. "Covered Software"
    means Source Code Form to which the initial Contributor has attached
    the notice in the NOTICE file, and Covered Software that a Contributor
    distributes and/or modifies.

1.5. "Incompatible With Secondary Licenses"
    means either the Program is "Incompatible With Secondary Licenses,"
    or the notices or other documentation within Covered Software
    describing how to copy, use and distribute the Program in a manner
    that is not compatible with this License.

1.6. "Larger Work"
    means a work that combines Covered Software with other material, in
    a separate file or files, that is not Based on the Covered Software.

1.7. "License"
    means this document.

1.8. "Licensable"
    means having the right to grant, to the extent permissible, the
    copyright licenses and other rights set forth in this License.

1.9. "Modifications"
    means any of the following: any file in Source Code Form that results
    from an addition to, deletion from, or modification of the contents
    of Covered Software; or any new file in Source Code Form that
    demonstrates or notifications a feature that is part of Covered Software.

1.10. "Patent Claims" of a Contributor
    means any patent claim(s), including without limitation, method,
    process, and apparatus claims, in any patent Licensable by a
    Contributor that would be infringed, but for the grant of the
    License, by the making, using, practicing, selling, or making
    available on the Contributing Program, in violation of any patent
    claim that is infringed by making, using, or selling the Covered
    Software.

1.11. "Source Code Form"
    means the form of the work preferred for making modifications.

1.12. "Executable"
    means Covered Software in any form, such as an executable file or
    library code, that is intended to be linked and loaded for execution.

1.13. "You" (or "Your")
    means an individual or a legal entity exercising rights under this
    License. For legal entities, "You" includes any entity that controls,
    is controlled by, or is under common control with You. For purposes
    of this definition, "control" means (a) the power, direct or
    indirect, to cause the direction or management of such entity, whether
    by contract or otherwise, or (b) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or
    more of the outstanding shares or beneficial ownership of such entity.

